pageContext.description: Oblong head, four sided with loop-like termination; faces divided by grooves into 4 segments: The top segment (which is divided by a distinct neck at the sides) is drilled.The middle segment below is also drilled. The top-middle segment has a cup-shaped hollow which may have held enamel; The bottom segment has one large hollow and 2 small on either face. The sides have one hollow each. The shank is made of a much yellower metal than the head.
pageContext.collection: Museum of Archaeology and Ethnology, Cambridge,No. 215,Murray Collection
